  <title>set_scale_with_gravity</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@accepts(gdouble, gdouble, Clutter.Gravity)
@returns(none)
def set_scale_with_gravity(scale_x, scale_y, gravity)
</code></synopsis>
<p>Scales an actor with the given factors around the given
center point. The center point is specified as one of the compass
directions in <link xref="Clutter.Gravity">Clutter.Gravity</link>. For example, setting it to north
will cause the top of the actor to remain unchanged and the rest of
the actor to expand left, right and downwards.</p><p>The <link xref="Clutter.Actor-scale-x">Clutter.Actor:scale-x</link> and <link xref="Clutter.Actor-scale-y">Clutter.Actor:scale-y</link> properties are
animatable.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>scale_x :</p></td>
<td><p>double factor to scale actor by horizontally.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>scale_y :</p></td>
<td><p>double factor to scale actor by vertically.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>gravity :</p></td>
<td><p>the location of the scale center expressed as a compass direction.</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 1.0</p>
